    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>The Occupational Education Program is a successor to the Department of Vocational Education, subsequently called the Department of Vocational Education and Practical Arts, which was established following the Smith-Hughes Act of 1917. It provided for the training of teachers of technical and industrial arts subjects.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The records of the Occupational Education Program contain a history of the program, annual reports (1919-1978), minutes of staff meetings (1950-1980), reports to the Extension Service and State Office of Vocational Education, program review and curriculum development files, correspondence and subject files.</p>
    </scopecontent>
